            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00DZ</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00DZ.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Strong morphisms of adjunctions and the Beck–Chevalley condition">Strong morphisms of adjunctions and the Beck–Chevalley condition</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The condition that a <fr:link href="jms-00DY.xml" title="Morphisms of adjunctions" addr="jms-00DY" type="local">lax morphism</fr:link> of adjunctions be <fr:link href="jms-00DY.xml" title="Morphisms of adjunctions" addr="jms-00DY" type="local">right strong</fr:link> is sometimes referred to as the <fr:em>Beck–Chevalley condition</fr:em>, e.g. by <fr:link href="uemura-2021-thesis.xml" title="Abstract and Concrete Type Theories" addr="uemura-2021-thesis" type="local">Uemura</fr:link>. Indeed, the <fr:link href="jms-00E0.xml" title="Mates between adjunctions" addr="jms-00E0" type="local">right-hand mates</fr:link> in a <fr:link href="jms-00DY.xml" title="Morphisms of adjunctions" addr="jms-00DY" type="local">lax morphism</fr:link> of adjunctions are occasionally referred to as <fr:em>Beck–Chevalley transformations</fr:em>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
